---
title: "Floor — Full Task Lifecycle"
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor U as User (Claude Code)
    participant M as Manager Session
    participant S as Scripts
    participant A as Agent Session

    note over U,A: ═══ PHASE 1 — PROMPT GENERATION ═══

    U->>M: Request task / describe feature
    activate M

    M->>M: Read prompting.md (triggered by CLAUDE.md response rule)

    M->>S: python check_cdocs.py
    activate S
    S-->>M: Exit 0 (all fresh) / Exit 1 (stale cdocs listed) / Exit 2 (error)
    deactivate S
    note right of S: ⚠ MIGRATION CANDIDATE<br/>Exit code currently<br/>interpreted by LLM,<br/>not enforced

    M->>M: Check Task Counter in status.md
    note right of M: ⚠ MIGRATION CANDIDATE<br/>Counter read + threshold<br/>check is pure text parsing—<br/>should be a script

    alt Task Counter ≥ 10
        M->>M: Generate arch health check prompt<br/>(from architecture-check.md)
        M-->>U: Output arch check prompt instead of task prompt
        note over U: Flow diverts to<br/>Architecture Health Check<br/>(see Diagram 4)
    end

    alt Interview needed
        M-->>U: Ask management decisions
        U->>M: Provide decisions
    end

    M->>M: Select cdocs via routing table
    M->>M: Compose prompt (manifest instruction,<br/>selected cdocs, task, plan-first rule,<br/>standards refs, close-prompt checklist)
    M-->>U: Output complete prompt text
    deactivate M

    note over U,A: ═══ PHASE 2 — USER HANDOFF (CRITICAL CHECKPOINT) ═══

    note over U: User reads prompt in terminal
    U->>U: Review prompt for accuracy
    U->>U: Modify prompt if needed<br/>(fix context, adjust scope,<br/>add/remove cdocs)
    U->>U: Open new Claude Code session

    note over U,A: ═══ PHASE 3 — AGENT EXECUTION ═══

    U->>A: Paste (modified) prompt
    activate A

    A->>A: Read manifest.md
    A->>A: Read all specified cdocs
    A->>A: Read standards (style.md, architecture.md if applicable)

    A-->>U: Present implementation plan
    deactivate A

    loop Plan Iteration
        U->>U: Evaluate plan
        alt Plan needs changes
            U->>A: Request modifications
            activate A
            A-->>U: Revised plan
            deactivate A
        else Plan acceptable
            U->>A: Approve plan (explicit or implicit)
        end
    end

    activate A
    A->>A: Implement changes<br/>(following style.md, checking architecture.md)

    note over U,A: ═══ PHASE 4 — VERIFICATION ═══

    A-->>U: Summary of changes + suggested test steps
    note right of A: Agent explicitly pauses here.<br/>Testing is user's responsibility.
    deactivate A

    U->>U: Run suggested tests
    U->>U: Verify implementation

    alt Issues found
        U->>A: Report issues
        activate A
        A->>A: Fix issues
        A-->>U: Updated summary + new test steps
        deactivate A
        note over U: User re-verifies
    end

    U->>A: Confirm task is done
    activate A

    note over U,A: ═══ PHASE 5 — CLEANUP (see Diagram 3 for detail) ═══

    A->>A: Update status.md (remove item, increment counter)
    A->>A: Update manifest.md (add/remove rows)
    A->>S: python check_cdoc_coverage.py
    activate S
    S-->>A: UNCOVERED files list / Exit 0
    deactivate S
    A->>A: Add uncovered files to cdoc sources
    A->>A: Update relevant cdocs

    A-->>U: Remind user to git commit
    deactivate A

    U->>U: git commit
